The paper deals with the expected complexity of random convex hulls, which is a topic in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves probabilistic analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of asymptotic notation and analysis of the expected complexity also suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper involves the study of convexity in higher dimensions, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
